text: The dainty frog (Cacosternum) is a genus of frogs in the family Pyxicephalidae found in southern and eastern Africa. Dainty frog may also refer to: * Dainty green tree frog (Litoria gracilenta), a frog in the family Hylidae native to eastern Queensland and northeastern New South Wales, Australia * Dainty nursery frog (Cophixalus exiguus), a frog in the family Microhylidae found in northeast Queensland, Australia Category:Animal common name disambiguation pages
